# Git Conventions

## Commits

- Only commit when explicitly asked
- Write concise messages (1–2 sentences) focused on **why**, not what
- Use complete sentences; match existing style (e.g. "updated README.md", "checkpoint — all working")
- Never commit `.env` or files with secrets
- Never skip hooks, force-push to main, or amend unless conditions are met

## Pull Requests

- Use `gh pr create` with Summary + Test plan sections
- Push branch with `-u` before creating PR
- Include all commits on the branch, not just the latest

## Branching

- Do not force-push unless explicitly requested
- Do not update git config
